                <h3>Bad Day</h3>
                <p>You made your choices without thinking.</p>
                <p>You answer my calls, but only to listen.</p>
                <p>You don’t want to say a word.</p>
                <p>You’d rather act like a child, full of anger.</p>
                <p>Everything is going wrong,</p>
                <p>With you.</p>
                <p>Even if it makes you walk away from me,</p>
                <p>It’s just another Bad Day.</p>
                <p>Everyone goes through it.</p>
                <h4>Verse 2:</h4>
                <p>You didn’t try hard enough.</p>
                <p>Now you’re changing your address.</p>
                <p>That’s the weakest solution you could find,</p>
                <p>Just to run away from what you really feel.</p>
                <p>You won’t get very far.</p>
                <p>Tell me how you’ll survive alone in loneliness,</p>
                <p>Without me to take care of you.</p>
                <h4>(Chorus)</h4>
                <p>Because love does that,</p>
                <p>It’s addictive like a drug.</p>
                <p>It controls us intensely.</p>
                <p>We become dependent on each other.</p>
                <p>And when we’re apart,</p>
                <p>It makes us</p>
                <p>Have flashbacks and want more.</p>
                <p>You won’t be able to resist.</p>
