<strong>Title</strong>

<pre>

</pre>


<strong>It Was All an Illusion</strong>


<p>We had wonderful months together,<br>
With unforgettable, pleasurable nights.<br>
I wasn’t ready to find out.<br>
It was only a matter of time<br>
For it all to end this way.</p>

<p>The whole truth would eventually appear.<br>
Your phone with changed passwords.<br>
You tried to hide everything,<br>
But you couldn’t.</p>

<p>You let this happen.<br>
I trusted all your words.</p>

<p>Now, our dinners together in the late afternoon<br>
Won’t be the same anymore.</p>

<p>I spent all the holidays alone,<br>
Watching our favorite shows,<br>
With those funny jokes<br>
That we used to laugh at all night long.</p>

<p>Did your heart feel love for me?</p>

<p>Some clothes you left here<br>
Will soon be thrown away.<br>
The photos from our last outing,<br>
Remembering how happy we were.</p>

<p>But all of this will now be just memories,<br>
That will fade with time.</p>

<p>Our lives will find other paths.</p>

<p>Now your voice is no longer heard here.<br>
We weren’t meant to be together.<br>
You didn’t take care of the one you claimed to love.</p>

<p>Everything that begins always has an end.<br>
Some end happily, others do not.</p>

<p>We used to play chess together;<br>
It was our favorite pastime.</p>

<p>The days went by, and everything changed.</p>

<p><strong>Chorus:</strong></p>

<p>Sorry, dear,<br>
But now<br>
Your lies are over.</p>

<p>I gave you the best of me.</p>

<p>It was beautiful, very magical while it lasted.<br>
Sometimes we choose wrongly.<br>
The heart has its limits.</p>

<p>I endured all the pain.</p>

<p>We started too soon,<br>
But the signs didn’t take long to appear.</p>

<p>Your strange behavior,<br>
Frequently sleeping away from home.</p>

<p>When I kissed you, you rejected me,<br>
Pretended that everything was fine.</p>

<p>Your eyes carried the lie.<br>
The truth always appears.</p>

<p>I was too fragile not to notice.</p>

<p>Sometimes we need to make<br>
Hard decisions<br>
To move forward.</p>

